President Obama has nominated Beverly Harvard and David Mark Singer to serve as U.S. Marshals. Beverly Harvard is currently the Director of Transportation Security Coordination at the United States Transportation Security Administration. She has a background in law enforcement, having worked for the City of Atlanta Police Department from 1973-2002, eventually becoming the Chief of Police. Harvard has a Bachelor of Arts Degree from Morris Brown College and a Master of Science Degree from Georgia State University. 

David Mark Singer is currently the Chief of Police for Whittier, California. He began his law enforcement career in 1979 at the Signal Hill, California Police Department and served there for 21 years, including five years as Chief of Police. Singer is also the chair of LA IMPACT, the Los Angeles countywide drug task force, and has served as an adjunct professor at California State University, Long Beach. He holds a bachelor's degree in criminal justice and a master's degree in public administration from California State University, Long Beach, and is a graduate of the FBI National Academy.